line.en: '...Yaaaawn...'
I try to stifle my yawn, as I watch the sky just\nbefore the break of dawn.
Today, it's my turn to watch it.
We have to watch over the sky before dawn, to see\nwhether or not there are any signs that the\nMorning Glory will occur.
'Aaaaah...'
But last night, I couldn't fall asleep until the\nusual time, so I didn't get enough sleep. I came\noutside after what only amounted to a short nap.
That's why I'm sleepy.
It's no good, if I stay still like this, I'm\ngonna fall asleep.
I'll try moving my body a little...
While going for a stroll, I go as far as the hill\nwhere the windmills stand.
As always, there's nothing unusual about the sky.
Of course, there's no one on the hill, and the\nlonely windmills turn.
I stand there a while, staring blankly at the\nsky.
So, it's dawn already...?
Time to go back.
Hmm?
Along the way, I pass by two girls.
Going for a stroll, this early in the morning?\nThat's strange...
But, I feel like I've seen them before... Is it\njust my imagination?
Meh, whatever.
Anyway, I'm heading back.
'It does feel good to go for a stroll in the\nmorning, after all.'
'Really? We're just walking, so I don't really\nsee why we have to do it so early in the\nmorning.'
'Well, you didn't have to come with me.'
'Well, if you go out for a stroll in the early\nmorning and get kidnapped, it'll cause problems\nfor me.'
'I'm not that stupid, you know!'
'Is that so? Hee hee.'
'Uhhh...'
'A...anyway! It feels nice to go for a stroll in\nthe morning!'
'There's nobody here, the air is fresh... It's\nlike stepping into another world.'
'That's why I like morning strolls.'
'Hey sis, this is the same world, by the way.'
'I know that! I know but that doesn't matter,\ndoes it?'
'This is why, sometimes, when I feel like I'm\ngetting lost in myself, I like to go for a\nmorning stroll and look at the view.'
'I see. That sounds like the kind of thing you'd\nsay.'
'Yoru, you're joking aren't you?'
'...I'll come with you on a stroll from time to\ntime. Well, it's nice to take a break.'
'Really?'
'...Yeah.'
